      "content_html": "<img src=\"https://i0.wp.com/boingboing.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/blood.jpg?fit=1200%2C800&amp;quality=60&amp;ssl=1\" style=\"width:100%;max-height:300px;object-fit:cover;\" />\n<a href=\"https://boingboing.net/2026/05/12/routine-blood-tests-show-16-markers-tied-to-ptsd-across-multiple-organ-systems.html\" rel=\"nofollow\" title=\"Routine blood tests show 16 markers tied to PTSD across multiple organ systems\"><img alt=\"PeopleImages/shutterstock.com\" class=\"webfeedsFeaturedVisual wp-post-image\" height=\"800\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/boingboing.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/blood.jpg?fit=1200%2C800&amp;quality=60&amp;ssl=1\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto; margin-bottom: 5px;\" width=\"1200\" /></a><p>A new study from Mass General Brigham, the Broad Trauma Initiative, and Harvard T.H. Chan School of Public Health found 16 blood biomarkers consistently linked to PTSD — all already on standard clinical lab panels: cholesterol, glucose, liver enzymes, albumin, bilirubin, white and red cell counts, the kind of routine results that stack up in a patient's chart during any ordinary physical. &#8212; <a class=\"read-more\" href=\"https://boingboing.net/2026/05/12/routine-blood-tests-show-16-markers-tied-to-ptsd-across-multiple-organ-systems.html\">Read the rest </a></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://boingboing.net/2026/05/12/routine-blood-tests-show-16-markers-tied-to-ptsd-across-multiple-organ-systems.html\">Routine blood tests show 16 markers tied to PTSD across multiple organ systems</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://boingboing.net\">Boing Boing</a>.</p>",
